
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `avahi-browse` baraye peyda kardane service-haye mojood dar shabakeye mahallie shoma (LAN) estefade mishavad.  In dastoor service-haye rooye shabake ro ke az Avahi estefade mikonan neshoon mide.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `avahi-browse -t _http._tcp` --> 🌐  Faghat service-haye HTTP TCP ro peyda mikone.  
    🔹 `avahi-browse -r _printer._tcp` --> 🖨️  Etela’at bishtar dar morede yek service printer khass ro neshoon mide.
    🔹 `avahi-browse --all`         --> 🔍  Hameye service-haye mojood ro neshoon mide.
    🔹 `avahi-browse -v`            --> 💬  Namayeshe etela'ate bishtar (verbose mode).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ avahi-browse _ssh._tcp

    🔹 Peyda kardane service-haye SSH TCP rooye shabake.

    $ avahi-browse -rt _http._tcp

    🔹 Peyda kardane hameye service-haye HTTP TCP be soorate real-time (ba update).

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ avahi-browse _afpovertcp._tcp

    🔹 Peida kardane service Apple Filing Protocol (AFP) rooye TCP. Agar hich chizi neshoon nade, yani hich service AFP rooye shabake nist.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `avahi-browse` command is used to discover services available on your local network (LAN). It displays network services that are using Avahi for service discovery.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `avahi-browse -t _http._tcp` --> 🌐  Only finds HTTP TCP services.
    🔹 `avahi-browse -r _printer._tcp` --> 🖨️  Shows more detailed information about a specific printer service.
    🔹 `avahi-browse --all`         --> 🔍  Shows all available services.
    🔹 `avahi-browse -v`            --> 💬  Verbose mode (shows more information).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ avahi-browse _ssh._tcp

    🔹 Discover SSH TCP services on the network.

    $ avahi-browse -rt _http._tcp

    🔹 Discover all HTTP TCP services in real-time (with updates).

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ avahi-browse _afpovertcp._tcp

    🔹 Find Apple Filing Protocol (AFP) services over TCP. If nothing is displayed, no AFP services are available on the network.
